<A NAME="chapterEnvelope2Ref"></A><h1>Envelopes of Curves in 2D<BR>
<I>Reference&nbsp;Manual</I></h1>
<P>

<p class="subtitle">Ron Wein</p>
<P>

<h2>Introduction</h2>


<A NAME="env2_ref_sec:intro"></A>
<P>

This package consists of functions that compute the lower (or upper)
envelope of a set of arbitrary curves in 2D. The output is
represented as an envelope diagram, namely a subdivision of the
<span class="math">x</span>-axis into intervals, such that the identity of the curves that
induce the envelope over each interval is unique.
<P>

